STATE of North Carolina
v.
Denzil Dequon FENNELL No. 314P18 Supreme Court of North Carolina. October 24, 2018. Denzil Dequon Fennell, for Fennell, Denzil Dequon Daniel P. O'Brien, Special Deputy Attorney General, for State of N.C. N. Lorrin Freeman, District Attorney, for State.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 20th of September 2018 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Wake County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 24th of October 2018."

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 20th of September 2018 by Defendant to Proceed In Forma Pauperis:

"Motion Allowed by order of the Court in conference, this the 24th of October 2018."

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 20th of September 2018 by Defendant to Appoint Counsel:

"Motion Dismissed as moot by order of the Court in conference, this the 24th of October 2018."
